The paper deals with communication protocols and information theory, which are both covered by the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category. The use of technology and the need for efficient communication suggest that the paper could also fit into the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) sub-categories. The focus on network communication and the use of bandwidth suggest that the paper could also fit into the cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) sub-category. Finally, the use of a protocol to facilitate communication suggests that the paper could also fit into the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category.
